WEBVTT

00:01.802 --> 00:03.169
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

00:03.169 --> 00:05.105
I WANT $100,000 IN CASH

00:05.105 --> 00:07.908
OR I'M GIVING AN INTERVIEW
TO ROSE ON THE 5:00 NEWS.

00:07.908 --> 00:10.844
THIS HERE IS RARIFIED AIR.
BE CAREFUL.

00:10.844 --> 00:13.313
IF SHE FINDS OUT I MORTGAGED
THIS HOUSE FOR YOU, SHE'S
GONNA BE DEVASTATED.

00:13.313 --> 00:15.115
YOU WILL HAVE SEVEN DAYS
TO VACATE THE PREMISES.

00:15.115 --> 00:16.583
HANNA ‐‐
THAT'S YOUR MAID'S NAME.

00:16.583 --> 00:19.085
HANNA, CAN I HAVE
SOME SPARKLING WATER, PLEASE?

00:19.085 --> 00:21.321
Katheryn: WILL YOU BE STAYING
FOR DINNER, CANDACE?

00:21.321 --> 00:22.956
NO, I HAVE
A VERY IMPORTANT MEETING,

00:22.956 --> 00:24.625
AND IF I'M NOT THERE,

00:24.625 --> 00:27.193
IT COULD CHANGE
A LOT OF PEOPLE'S LIVES.

00:27.193 --> 00:29.295
ROSE,
I HAVE A STORY FOR YOU.

00:29.295 --> 00:30.697
IT'S ABOUT JUDGE CRYER.

00:36.469 --> 00:38.238
MA, WHY ARE YOU SITTING IN
THE DARK BY YOURSELF LIKE THAT?

00:40.006 --> 00:41.307
I GOT YOUR SOUP.

00:41.307 --> 00:44.878
NEW LITTLE FAVORITE CORNER STORE
UP THE STREET.

00:44.878 --> 00:46.680
MWAH.

00:46.680 --> 00:48.549
IT'S PROBABLY COLD BY NOW,

00:48.549 --> 00:51.752
BUT MAKE SOME CRACKERS WITH IT
OR SOMETHING.

00:54.487 --> 00:57.457
MAMA,
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

01:01.434 --> 01:05.806
I PRIDE MYSELF ON BEING
AN INDEPENDENT WOMAN.

01:09.876 --> 01:13.714
I BOUGHT THIS HOUSE
WHEN I WAS 21 YEARS OLD.

01:13.714 --> 01:16.750
HAD YOU AND YOUR SISTER
ON MY HIP.

01:16.750 --> 01:19.853
THREE AND FOUR YEARS OLD.

01:19.853 --> 01:23.690
I WORKED TWO JOBS WHEN
YOUR FATHER WALKED OUT ON ME.

01:23.690 --> 01:26.560
I DIDN'T CRUMBLE.

01:26.560 --> 01:29.095
I DIDN'T CRY.

01:29.095 --> 01:31.397
AND I DIDN'T EVEN COMPLAIN.

01:31.397 --> 01:33.934
I DID WHAT I HAD TO DO.

01:33.934 --> 01:36.570
[ Voice breaking ] AND I FOUND
THE STRENGTH TO DO IT...

01:36.570 --> 01:38.972
[SOBS]

01:38.972 --> 01:42.776
THROUGH THE GRACE OF GOD.

01:42.776 --> 01:47.347
AND THEN THERE'S YOU
AND YOUR SISTER.

01:47.347 --> 01:49.583
[ SCOFFS ]

01:49.583 --> 01:50.951
[ SIGHS ]

01:50.951 --> 01:53.754
WHEN SHE WENT WRONG,
I WAS DETERMINED

01:53.754 --> 01:59.159
I WASN'T GONNA RAISE ANOTHER
ANGRY, CRIMINAL BLACK MAN.

01:59.159 --> 02:01.802
I WAS GONNA RAISE
A MAN WITH CHARACTER

02:01.802 --> 02:07.073
WHO WOULD BE SMART
AND DIGNIFIED.

02:07.073 --> 02:11.612
AND YOU GREW UP TO BE
JUST THAT.

02:11.612 --> 02:13.580
[ SOBS ]

02:16.182 --> 02:18.885
YOU MADE ME PROUD EVERY DAY
THAT I WAS YOUR MOTHER ‐‐

02:18.885 --> 02:20.721
EVERY DAY.

02:20.721 --> 02:23.156
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]
I KNOW THAT, MOMMY.

02:23.156 --> 02:26.059
YOU'RE STARTING TO SCARE ME.
I MEAN, WHAT'S GOING ON?

02:26.059 --> 02:28.128
DON'T ACT
LIKE YOU DON'T KNOW.

02:28.128 --> 02:30.664
WHAT?

02:30.664 --> 02:31.932
[ SCOFFS ]

02:31.932 --> 02:34.601
IS THERE SOMETHING YOU WANT
TO TELL ME, BENNY?

02:38.004 --> 02:39.372
MAMA ‐‐
OH, PLEASE.

02:39.372 --> 02:41.441
DON'T MAKE ME
DRAG IT OUT OF YOU.

02:41.441 --> 02:42.976
JUST TELL IT TO ME, BENNY.

02:42.976 --> 02:45.546
PLEASE SAY IT TO ME
BEFORE I SAY IT TO YOU.

02:45.546 --> 02:47.514
PLEASE?

02:47.514 --> 02:50.483
MAMA, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

02:50.483 --> 02:52.452
SO, YOU'RE REALLY NOT GONNA
TELL ME?

02:52.452 --> 02:55.556
I WAS HOPING
YOU WOULD HAVE TOLD ME.

02:57.791 --> 03:00.026
I'VE BEEN HOLDING ON
TO ONE CENT OF HOPE FOR YOU ‐‐

03:00.026 --> 03:01.568
JUST ONE.

03:10.811 --> 03:13.146
YOU MORTGAGED MY HOUSE,
BENNY?

03:17.417 --> 03:20.654
MAMA ‐‐
YOU MORTGAGED MY HOUSE?

03:23.189 --> 03:25.759
LOOK AT ME!

03:25.759 --> 03:28.394
YEAH.

03:28.394 --> 03:29.663
I DID.

03:29.663 --> 03:30.797
OKAY?

03:30.797 --> 03:34.400
I'M SORRY.

03:34.400 --> 03:35.902
I MEAN,
CANDACE IS IN TROUBLE.

03:35.902 --> 03:37.504
[ SIGHS ]

03:41.542 --> 03:44.077
WILL YOU JUST LET ME EXPLAIN
THIS TO YOU?

03:44.077 --> 03:46.379
MAMA.

03:59.637 --> 04:02.397
MAMA, WILL YOU JUST LET ME
EXPLAIN THIS TO YOU?

04:04.405 --> 04:06.648
PLEASE?

04:06.648 --> 04:07.916
MAMA, STOP PACKING.

04:07.916 --> 04:10.819
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO ‐‐
WAIT TILL THEY COME

04:10.819 --> 04:13.588
AND THROW EVERYTHING
OUT ON THE STREET?

04:13.588 --> 04:16.290
HOW COULD YOU DO THIS
TO ME, TO US?

04:16.290 --> 04:17.992
WE ARE HOMELESS, BENNY.

04:17.992 --> 04:19.494
WE'RE NOT HOMELESS,
ALL RIGHT?

04:19.494 --> 04:20.762
I'M GONNA SELL MY TRUCK.

04:20.762 --> 04:23.397
I'LL GO DOWN THERE TONIGHT.
I'LL SELL IT RIGHT NOW.

04:23.397 --> 04:25.567
SELLING YOUR TRUCK
AIN'T GONNA FIX THIS.

04:25.567 --> 04:27.502
THEY WANT ALL THE MONEY,
BENNY ‐‐

04:27.502 --> 04:29.270
$50,000.

04:29.270 --> 04:30.672
THEN I'LL TALK
TO THEM ABOUT IT, OKAY?

04:30.672 --> 04:33.174
I'LL GET SOMETHING
WORKED OUT.

04:33.174 --> 04:34.976
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

04:34.976 --> 04:37.479
[ Crying ]
WHY'D YOU DO THIS TO ME?

04:37.479 --> 04:39.714
THIS AIN'T EVEN LIKE YOU.

04:39.714 --> 04:41.816
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

04:41.816 --> 04:42.817
ANSWER ME!

04:42.817 --> 04:44.953
MAMA,
YOU WERE IN THE HOSPITAL.

04:44.953 --> 04:46.621
AND CANDACE WAS IN TROUBLE.

04:46.621 --> 04:51.660
OOH, I KNEW IT.
I KNEW IT WAS HER.

04:51.660 --> 04:52.961
MAMA, SHE WAS IN TROUBLE.

04:52.961 --> 04:54.796
THAT GIRL WASN'T IN
NO TROUBLE.

04:54.796 --> 04:55.964
SHE WAS CONNING YOU.

04:55.964 --> 04:58.767
SHE WASN'T CONNING ME.
SHE WAS.

04:58.767 --> 05:01.836
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.

05:01.836 --> 05:04.706
HOW DID SHE KNOW
MY HOUSE WAS IN YOUR NAME?

05:04.706 --> 05:07.416
[ SIGHS ] BECAUSE I TOLD HER.
MM‐HMM.

05:07.416 --> 05:10.719
AND HOW LONG AFTER THAT
DID SHE GET IN TROUBLE?

05:10.719 --> 05:13.221
MAMA ‐‐
ANSWER ME.

05:13.221 --> 05:15.890
THE NEXT WEEK.

05:15.890 --> 05:19.293
SEE?
THAT'S WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.

05:19.293 --> 05:21.129
THIS AIN'T NO COINCIDENCE.

05:21.129 --> 05:22.664
THAT'S WHAT SHE DOES.

05:22.664 --> 05:24.065
SHE WASN'T CONNING.
I'M TRYING TO TELL YOU.

05:24.065 --> 05:25.133
OH, HOW CAN YOU SAY THAT?

05:25.133 --> 05:26.635
'CAUSE SHE WASN'T, OKAY?

05:26.635 --> 05:30.038
SHE CALLED ME TO PICK HER UP
LATE ONE NIGHT.

05:30.038 --> 05:31.473
YOU KNOW HOW SHE GOT IN TROUBLE
WITH THE CAR.

05:31.473 --> 05:34.543
MOMMY,
WHEN I WENT TO GO GET HER,

05:34.543 --> 05:36.310
I WALKED RIGHT PAST HER.
OKAY?

05:36.310 --> 05:38.947
I DIDN'T EVEN RECOGNIZE HER,
SHE WAS BEAT SO BAD.

05:38.947 --> 05:41.315
BY THAT BOY?
YEAH.

05:41.315 --> 05:43.084
I TOOK HER TO THE SAME HOSPITAL
YOU WERE AT.

05:43.084 --> 05:45.153
SHE WAS ONE FLOOR
DOWN BELOW YOU. ALL RIGHT?

05:45.153 --> 05:47.088
I GUESS SHE OWED HIM
SOME TYPE OF MONEY.

05:47.088 --> 05:50.091
YOU KNOW, HE SAID THAT IF
HE DIDN'T GET IT,

05:50.091 --> 05:51.660
HE WAS GONNA KILL HER.

05:51.660 --> 05:54.228
MAMA, HE DAMN NEAR DID.
SHE WAS ‐‐ SHE WAS IN BAD SHAPE.

05:54.228 --> 05:56.030
I'M TRYING TO TELL YOU.

05:56.030 --> 05:57.265
THAT'S THE LIFE SHE CHOSE,
BENNY.

05:57.265 --> 05:58.867
MOMMY, THAT'S STILL
YOUR DAUGHTER.

05:58.867 --> 05:59.868
THAT GIRL IS WICKED.

05:59.868 --> 06:01.436
STILL YOUR CHILD,
THOUGH, OKAY?

06:01.436 --> 06:02.737
DO YOU HEAR WHAT I SAID?

06:02.737 --> 06:04.506
THEY WERE WILLING
TO KILL HER.

06:04.506 --> 06:07.716
WELL...
[SNIFFLES]

06:07.716 --> 06:10.519
...MAYBE IF SHE'D HAVE GONE ON,
SHE'D HAVE FOUND SOME PEACE.

06:10.519 --> 06:13.622
MAMA,
YOU DON'T MEAN THAT.

06:13.622 --> 06:16.290
DON'T YOU TELL ME
WHAT I MEAN.

06:16.290 --> 06:19.227
THAT GIRL AIN'T BEEN NOTHING
BUT TROUBLE

06:19.227 --> 06:23.131
FROM THE TIME I GOT PREGNANT
WITH HER, ON THROUGH MY LABOR.

06:23.131 --> 06:26.501
I WAS SICK AS A DOG
EVERY DAY.

06:26.501 --> 06:29.671
THAT CHILD FLIPPED OVER
IN MY WOMB

06:29.671 --> 06:31.573
AND ALMOST KILLED ME.

06:31.573 --> 06:35.409
IT'S LIKE SHE AIN'T NEVER WANTED
TO BE HERE.

06:35.409 --> 06:38.847
MAYBE IF SHE'D HAVE GONE ON
OR PASSED ON,

06:38.847 --> 06:42.150
MAYBE THEN SHE'D HAVE FOUND
SOME PEACE,

06:42.150 --> 06:47.155
PUT US BOTH
OUT OF OUR MISERY.

06:50.024 --> 06:52.160
WELL, FOR SOMEONE WHO IS ALWAYS
GRABBING THE BIBLE,

06:52.160 --> 06:53.628
THAT'S
SOME REAL CHRISTIAN TALK.

06:53.628 --> 06:56.931
DON'T YOU DARE
THROW GOD IN MY FACE!

06:56.931 --> 06:58.366
[ SIGHS ]

06:58.366 --> 07:02.871
LOOK, YOU'RE UPSET, OKAY?
I GET IT.

07:02.871 --> 07:05.206
YOU'RE REALLY UPSET
RIGHT NOW.

07:05.206 --> 07:07.115
I'M GONNA LET YOU CALM DOWN.
ALL RIGHT?

07:07.115 --> 07:08.783
I'M GONNA GO GRAB
A SIP OF WATER.

07:08.783 --> 07:10.419
LET'S CALM DOWN,
I'M GONNA FORGET

07:10.419 --> 07:12.286
THAT YOU JUST SAID THAT
ABOUT CANDACE.

07:13.287 --> 07:15.690
[ SOBS ]

07:15.690 --> 07:17.492
SHE GOT TO YOU, TOO, HUH?

07:17.492 --> 07:19.561
[ SIGHS ]

07:19.561 --> 07:22.296
DON'T YOU KNOW THAT GIRL DON'T
CARE ABOUT NOBODY BUT HERSELF?

07:22.296 --> 07:25.099
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND,
SHE CAN'T?

07:25.099 --> 07:26.968
SHE CAN'T.

07:26.968 --> 07:30.038
IT AIN'T IN HER TO LOVE ANYTHING
OR ANYBODY.

07:30.038 --> 07:31.139
SHE GOT A BABY SOMEWHERE.

07:31.139 --> 07:32.974
SHE PROBABLY DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHERE HE IS.

07:32.974 --> 07:37.679
IT JUST AIN'T IN HER
TO CARE.

07:37.679 --> 07:40.181
YEAH, BUT, MAMA, IT AIN'T IN YOU
TO HATE NOBODY LIKE THAT.

07:40.181 --> 07:42.551
I DON'T HATE HER.
WELL, YOU MUST.

07:42.551 --> 07:44.318
YOU CAME IN HERE. YOU JUST
WISHED MY SISTER WAS DEAD.

07:44.318 --> 07:48.289
JUST STOP IT.
YOU JUST STOP IT.

07:48.289 --> 07:51.025
[ SIGHS ]

07:51.025 --> 07:52.627
LOOK, I'M SORRY.

07:52.627 --> 07:53.795
I'M SORRY I DID THAT.

07:53.795 --> 07:55.964
I'M SORRY I SAVED
YOUR DAUGHTER'S LIFE.

07:55.964 --> 07:57.098
ALL RIGHT?

07:57.098 --> 07:58.366
BUT YOU WOULD HAVE DONE
THE SAME THING,

07:58.366 --> 07:59.501
HAD YOU SEEN HER THAT NIGHT.

07:59.501 --> 08:01.970
MAMA, I KNOW IT.
I KNOW YOU.

08:01.970 --> 08:04.706
I'M GONNA SELL MY TRUCK,
ALL RIGHT?

08:04.706 --> 08:05.840
I'M GONNA SELL IT
RIGHT NOW.

08:05.840 --> 08:07.215
I'M GONNA BRING IN
AS MUCH AS I CAN.

08:07.215 --> 08:10.985
YOUR TRUCK AIN'T WORTH
NO $50,000.

08:10.985 --> 08:12.854
[ SNIFFLES ]

08:12.854 --> 08:15.223
THEY WANT IT ALL, BENNY.

08:15.223 --> 08:17.426
THEY WANT IT ALL.

08:17.426 --> 08:19.694
ALL RIGHT, WELL...

08:19.694 --> 08:21.262
I'LL DO WHAT I CAN, THOUGH,
ALL RIGHT?

08:21.262 --> 08:23.164
I [ SIGHS ]

08:23.164 --> 08:26.535
I GOT TO TRY SOMETHING, MAMA.

08:26.535 --> 08:29.370
I'M GONNA FIX THIS.

08:29.370 --> 08:30.972
[ SOBS ]

08:30.972 --> 08:34.242
MAMA, LOOK AT ME.

08:34.242 --> 08:36.277
STOP CRYING.
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THIS, OKAY?

08:36.277 --> 08:39.247
I'M GONNA FIX THIS.

08:47.689 --> 08:48.790
ON THE 12th OF AUGUST,

08:48.790 --> 08:50.925
I LOOK FORWARD TO
YOUR IMMEDIATE RESPONSE.

08:50.925 --> 08:52.026
OKAY? THEN, FINISH IT.

08:52.026 --> 08:53.662
THANKS, ANNE.
GO ON.

08:57.298 --> 09:01.436
CLOSE THE DOOR, PLEASE,
ON YOUR WAY OUT.

09:01.436 --> 09:03.204
WHAT DID YOU DO?

09:03.204 --> 09:05.139
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

09:05.139 --> 09:07.716
DON'T STAND THERE EATING CANDY,
BEING ALL COY WITH ME, DAVID.

09:07.716 --> 09:08.750
WHAT HAPPENED?

09:08.750 --> 09:09.918
OH, WITH CANDACE.

09:09.918 --> 09:10.952
YES.

09:10.952 --> 09:13.121
I DECIDED NOT TO PLAY
BY HER RULES.

09:13.121 --> 09:14.222
CALLED HER BLUFF.

09:14.222 --> 09:16.491
YOU CALLED HER BLUFF.

09:16.491 --> 09:18.760
CAN'T LET THESE PEOPLE THINK
THEY HAVE THE UPPER HAND.

09:18.760 --> 09:20.261
SHE'S INSANE, DAVID.

09:20.261 --> 09:21.830
WHY ARE YOU SO UPSET?

09:21.830 --> 09:23.698
IT WORKED, DIDN'T IT?
DID IT?

09:23.698 --> 09:26.234
WELL,
SHE DIDN'T CALL THE NEWS.

09:26.234 --> 09:27.235
ROSE.

09:27.235 --> 09:29.438
DO YOU KNOW ROSE?

09:29.438 --> 09:32.106
THE REPORTER.
'COURSE I KNOW ROSE.

09:32.106 --> 09:34.108
SHE CALLED MY OFFICE,
TALKED TO MY SECRETARY,

09:34.108 --> 09:36.410
SAID SHE HAD A FEW QUESTIONS
SHE WOULD LIKE TO ASK ME.

09:36.410 --> 09:38.312
WHAT KIND OF QUESTIONS?

09:38.312 --> 09:40.415
QUESTIONS ABOUT HOW I FEEL

09:40.415 --> 09:43.084
ABOUT ELECTED OFFICIALS
AND PROSTITUTES.

09:43.084 --> 09:46.287
SHE SAID THAT?

09:46.287 --> 09:48.089
YES.
SHE SAID THAT.

09:48.089 --> 09:49.991
SO, YOU DID NOT PAY HER?

09:49.991 --> 09:54.028
NO. WANTED HER TO KNOW
WHO WAS HOLDING ALL THE CARDS.

09:54.028 --> 09:56.130
WELL, CLEARLY SHE'S HOLDING
ALL THE CARDS, DAVID.

09:56.130 --> 09:57.866
I'M TELLING YOU,
SHE'S INSANE.

09:57.866 --> 09:59.000
YOU NEED TO PAY HER.

09:59.000 --> 10:01.002
I'LL CALL HER NOW.

10:01.002 --> 10:03.472
YES, NOW.
PLEASE.

10:03.472 --> 10:04.873
THANK YOU.

10:08.049 --> 10:10.485
[ SIGHS ]

10:12.554 --> 10:14.556
[ DOOR OPENS ]

10:32.974 --> 10:35.243
GOOD MORNING.

10:35.243 --> 10:37.946
GOOD MORNING.

10:37.946 --> 10:40.782
I KEEP FINDING YOU IN HERE
EVERY TIME I COME IN HERE.

10:43.752 --> 10:46.220
MAKES ME THINK I'M NOT DOING
MY JOB TOO WELL

10:46.220 --> 10:48.022
IF YOU HAVE TO WASH
EVERY DAY.

10:48.022 --> 10:49.691
YOU'RE DOING A GREAT JOB.

10:49.691 --> 10:51.793
SOMETIMES
I WAKE UP RESTLESS.

10:51.793 --> 10:53.194
OH, PLEASE.
LET ME DO THAT.

10:53.194 --> 10:54.663
I GOT IT.
WELL, I CAN AT L‐‐

10:54.663 --> 10:57.365
I SAID I HAVE IT.

10:57.365 --> 11:00.535
I'M SORRY.

11:03.638 --> 11:06.314
CAN YOU GO HELP CELINE
WITH BREAKFAST, PLEASE?

11:06.314 --> 11:08.783
YES, MA'AM.

11:20.294 --> 11:21.630
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

11:21.630 --> 11:23.765
[ SIGHS ]

11:40.549 --> 11:42.617
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

11:42.617 --> 11:43.718
DOOR, HANNA.

11:51.359 --> 11:53.161
KATH!
SHE'S IN THE DINING ROOM.

11:53.161 --> 11:54.896
THANK YOU.

11:54.896 --> 11:57.065
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

11:57.065 --> 11:59.668
YOU'RE STILL
IN YOUR BED CLOTHES.

11:59.668 --> 12:01.169
GOOD MORNING.

12:01.169 --> 12:03.371
GOOD TO SEE YOU, TOO.

12:03.371 --> 12:04.639
I'M SORRY.

12:04.639 --> 12:06.515
UH, GOOD MORNING.

12:06.515 --> 12:08.349
THAT'S BETTER.

12:08.349 --> 12:09.751
WOULD YOU LIKE
SOME BREAKFAST?

12:09.751 --> 12:10.952
NO.

12:10.952 --> 12:12.487
HOW ARE YOU?

12:12.487 --> 12:14.989
OKAY.
ENOUGH WITH THE PLEASANTRIES.

12:14.989 --> 12:17.091
WHAT'S GOING ON?
I THINK I HAVE A PROBLEM.

12:17.091 --> 12:21.062
YOU JUST FOUND <i>ONE?</i>

12:21.062 --> 12:22.697
WELL, LET'S SEE.

12:22.697 --> 12:25.066
I THINK YOU EAT TOO MUCH.

12:25.066 --> 12:27.502
YOU GET A LITTLE LOUD
EVERY NOW AND THEN.

12:27.502 --> 12:29.403
AND YOU DRIVE
LIKE A BAT OUT OF HELL.

12:29.403 --> 12:31.940
ARE YOU DONE?

12:31.940 --> 12:34.075
AND YOU STILL THINK
YOU'RE 25.

12:34.075 --> 12:35.409
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

12:35.409 --> 12:37.546
THIS IS SERIOUS.
I HAVE A PROBLEM.

12:37.546 --> 12:38.847
GET IN LINE.

12:38.847 --> 12:41.950
I THINK
DAVID IS HAVING AN AFFAIR.

12:41.950 --> 12:43.117
[ LAUGHS ]

12:44.285 --> 12:46.120
WHAT IS SO FUNNY?

12:46.120 --> 12:50.425
MR. CONSERVATIVE?
ALWAYS‐BY‐THE‐BOOK DAVID?

12:50.425 --> 12:52.193
OH, I DON'T THINK SO.

12:52.193 --> 12:53.862
WELL,
SOMETHING IS GOING ON.

12:53.862 --> 12:56.264
ARE YOU SURE?
YES.

12:56.264 --> 12:58.567
I THINK.

12:58.567 --> 13:00.735
PROBABLY.

13:00.735 --> 13:02.837
EITHER HE IS OR HE ISN'T.

13:02.837 --> 13:05.840
WELL, FOR THE PAST TWO WEEKS,
HE'S BEEN VERY DISTANT.

13:05.840 --> 13:07.716
HE'S TRYING TO RUN
FOR OFFICE.

13:07.716 --> 13:09.150
NO, NO.

13:09.150 --> 13:12.086
I KNOW THIS MAN.
I CAN SET MY WATCH BY HIM.

13:12.086 --> 13:14.388
HE IS THE EPITOME
OF PREDICTABILITY.

13:14.388 --> 13:15.790
SOMETHING IS GOING ON.

13:15.790 --> 13:17.225
I THINK
YOU'RE OVERREACTING.

13:17.225 --> 13:18.493
I AM NOT.

13:18.493 --> 13:20.094
DO YOU REMEMBER THE LAST TIME

13:20.094 --> 13:22.330
YOU THOUGHT
DAVID WAS HAVING AN AFFAIR?

13:22.330 --> 13:24.032
HE WAS PLANNING
YOUR SURPRISE BIRTHDAY PARTY.

13:24.032 --> 13:25.233
THIS IS DIFFERENT.

13:25.233 --> 13:27.135
SO, YOU'RE NOT GONNA KILL
THE PARTY PLANNER?

13:27.135 --> 13:29.671
SHE WAS FLIRTING WITH HIM.

13:29.671 --> 13:31.573
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:31.573 --> 13:36.044
VERONICA...
DAVID IS NO FOOL.

13:36.044 --> 13:38.179
HE KNOWS
YOU WILL FIERCELY FIGHT

13:38.179 --> 13:40.649
TO PROTECT YOUR FAMILY
AND YOUR FUTURE.

13:40.649 --> 13:42.451
NOW, GO HOME.

13:42.451 --> 13:46.320
SO, YOU THINK
THAT I AM OVERREACTING?

13:46.320 --> 13:47.822
I KNOW IT.

13:47.822 --> 13:50.024
I KNOW <i>YOU.</i>

13:50.024 --> 13:52.494
IF SOMETHING IS GOING ON,
TIME WILL REVEAL IT.

13:52.494 --> 13:55.229
I AM NOT A FAN OF WAITING
FOR FATHER TIME.

13:55.229 --> 13:57.532
AND HE IS NOT A FAN
OF YOUR CROW'S‐FEET.

13:57.532 --> 14:00.535
KATHERYN CRYER,
THAT'S JUST AWFUL.

14:00.535 --> 14:02.471
[ CHUCKLES ]
I HAVE THEM, TOO.

14:02.471 --> 14:05.540
GO HOME.
GREAT.

14:05.540 --> 14:07.982
WHAT A WAY TO TREAT
A FRIEND IN NEED.

14:07.982 --> 14:09.217
HMM!

14:09.217 --> 14:11.686
AND I DO NOT HAVE
CROW'S‐FEET.

14:11.686 --> 14:13.154
HAH!
GOOD DAY.

14:13.154 --> 14:14.723
BYE.

14:14.723 --> 14:16.257
[ MOUTHING WORDS ]

14:19.594 --> 14:21.596
[ DOOR OPENS ]

14:27.569 --> 14:29.471
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

14:29.471 --> 14:30.572
WHERE'S JIM?

14:30.572 --> 14:33.074
I'LL BE HANDLING THIS.

14:33.074 --> 14:35.510
YOU AGAIN.

14:35.510 --> 14:37.111
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

14:37.111 --> 14:38.880
HE CAN'T HANDLE
BEING ALONE WITH ME?

14:38.880 --> 14:41.015
THIS DOESN'T NEED TO
INVOLVE JIM.

14:41.015 --> 14:42.283
HMM.

14:42.283 --> 14:45.787
YOU KNOW,
THIS TURNS HIM ON ‐‐

14:45.787 --> 14:46.988
LIVING ON THE EDGE.

14:46.988 --> 14:49.223
HE'S A BIT OF
AN ADRENALINE JUNKIE.

14:49.223 --> 14:52.494
NOT LIKE YOU,
MR. PLAY‐IT‐SAFE.

14:52.494 --> 14:54.763
YOU GOT TO GET THAT STICK
OUT OF YOUR ASS,

14:54.763 --> 14:57.666
UNLESS YOU'RE INTO
THAT SORT OF THING.

14:57.666 --> 14:58.767
HUH?

15:01.503 --> 15:02.837
THERE'S YOUR MONEY.

15:02.837 --> 15:03.838
PICK IT UP.

15:05.674 --> 15:07.782
YOUNG LADY.
PICK IT UP NOW!

15:19.961 --> 15:25.199
DON'T YOU EVER THROW ANYTHING
AT ME AGAIN, EVER.

15:25.199 --> 15:29.771
THERE'S $100,000
IN THIS BAG.

15:29.771 --> 15:34.408
I WOULD NOT GIVE A DAMN
IF IT WAS A MILLION DOLLARS.

15:34.408 --> 15:38.079
YOU THINK
YOU'RE BETTER THAN ME, HUH?

15:38.079 --> 15:41.583
YOU THINK, BECAUSE YOU'RE RICH,
YOU CAN TREAT ME LIKE CRAP?

15:41.583 --> 15:43.752
I THINK
WE'RE GETTING OFF COURSE HERE.

15:43.752 --> 15:45.186
YOU THREW THAT BAG AT ME

15:45.186 --> 15:47.756
LIKE I WAS A DOG IN THE STREET
YOU WERE THROWING A BONE TO.

15:47.756 --> 15:49.591
YOU WANT THE MONEY OR NOT?

15:49.591 --> 15:52.527
IF YOU EVER
DISRESPECT ME AGAIN,

15:52.527 --> 15:56.498
NOTHING IN THAT BAG
WILL MATTER.

16:00.068 --> 16:02.937
SIGN THE PAPERS.

16:15.323 --> 16:17.391
[ CURRENCY BUNDLES
RUSTLING ]

16:19.694 --> 16:22.631
I DON'T SEE ANY KEYS
IN THIS BAG.

16:22.631 --> 16:25.366
BECAUSE WE'RE NOT GIVING YOU
A CAR.

16:25.366 --> 16:28.870
BUT I SAID I WANTED
A CONVERTIBLE.

16:28.870 --> 16:30.672
I SAID
YOU'RE NOT GETTING ONE.

16:30.672 --> 16:32.641
[ Chuckling ] MAN.

16:32.641 --> 16:36.110
YOU MUST THINK I'M KIDDING.

16:36.110 --> 16:39.514
DIDN'T ROSE CALL JIM?

16:39.514 --> 16:42.283
WHAT DID YOU HAVE TO DO
WITH THAT?

16:42.283 --> 16:46.688
I DIDN'T TELL HER
ANYTHING...YET.

16:46.688 --> 16:51.392
I SAID THAT I MAY KNOW SOMEONE
WHO IS DEALING WITH PROSTITUTES

16:51.392 --> 16:54.062
AND SHE SHOULD TALK TO
JUDGE CRYER ABOUT IT.

16:54.062 --> 16:56.330
[ SIGHS ]
THIS IS SO FOOLISH.

16:56.330 --> 16:57.899
NO.

16:57.899 --> 17:00.535
WHAT'S FOOLISH IS
YOU PLAYING GAMES WITH ME.

17:00.535 --> 17:03.438
I THINK YOU'RE CRAZY,

17:03.438 --> 17:06.014
BUT I DON'T THINK
YOU'RE THAT CRAZY.

17:06.014 --> 17:09.350
HMM.

17:09.350 --> 17:12.186
[ SIGHS ]

17:14.288 --> 17:16.024
OKAY.

17:18.326 --> 17:19.794
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

17:22.263 --> 17:23.698
[ GASPS ]

17:23.698 --> 17:24.999
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

17:24.999 --> 17:27.368
[ Voice breaking ] PLEASE.
STOP HITTING ME.

17:27.368 --> 17:30.271
THAT HURTS.
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

17:30.271 --> 17:31.773
PLEASE! I WON'T SCREAM.

17:31.773 --> 17:33.241
YOUNG LADY.
I WON'T SAY ANYTHING.

17:33.241 --> 17:35.043
I WON'T TELL ANYBODY. I WON'T.
Shh!

17:35.043 --> 17:37.178
PLEASE! PLEASE!
Shh!

17:37.178 --> 17:38.447
STOP IT!

17:38.447 --> 17:40.482
WHY?

17:42.651 --> 17:46.387
WHY STOP?

17:46.387 --> 17:48.056
DO YOU WANT TO SEE
HOW FAR THIS CAN GO?

17:48.056 --> 17:49.891
CANDACE.

17:49.891 --> 17:51.460
[ SCOFFS ]

17:51.460 --> 17:54.195
YOU KNOW MY NAME NOW?

17:54.195 --> 17:59.333
MAYBE I WANT $100,000
FROM YOU, TOO.

17:59.333 --> 18:01.402
DO YOU SEE HOW EASY THIS IS?

18:03.271 --> 18:06.548
YOU AND YOUR IVORY TOWER.

18:06.548 --> 18:11.385
ONE WORD FROM ME,
AND IT ALL COMES CRUMBLING DOWN.

18:16.057 --> 18:17.125
OKAY.

18:17.125 --> 18:19.661
O‐‐ WHAT?
SORRY?

18:19.661 --> 18:20.662
OKAY.

18:20.662 --> 18:21.730
OH.

18:21.730 --> 18:23.965
"OKAY" WHAT?

18:23.965 --> 18:25.700
OKAY, YOU WIN.

18:34.543 --> 18:35.744
I WIN, HUH?

18:35.744 --> 18:37.078
MM‐HMM.

18:37.078 --> 18:39.514
I ALREADY KNEW THAT.

18:39.514 --> 18:41.950
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

18:41.950 --> 18:44.352
WHERE IS MY CAR?

18:44.352 --> 18:48.457
YOU'LL GET IT.

18:48.457 --> 18:50.258
MM.

18:50.258 --> 18:52.494
OKAY.

18:52.494 --> 18:55.196
YOU LEARN FAST.

18:55.196 --> 18:57.766
I WANT MY CAR TODAY.

18:57.766 --> 19:01.402
RED, LIKE MY SKIRT.

19:01.402 --> 19:03.605
YOU LIKE MY SKIRT?

19:06.047 --> 19:08.382
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

19:12.621 --> 19:13.922
OH.

19:13.922 --> 19:15.690
YOU WANT TO KNOW
THE DIFFERENCE

19:15.690 --> 19:19.327
BETWEEN YOU
AND THE COMMON STREET THUG?

19:19.327 --> 19:20.995
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

19:20.995 --> 19:22.531
"RARIFIED AIR"?

19:22.531 --> 19:25.133
YOU KNOW
WHAT THE DIFFERENCE IS?

19:25.133 --> 19:27.902
NOT A DAMN THING.

19:29.771 --> 19:31.005
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

19:36.911 --> 19:41.349
YOU REALLY WANT TO PLAY THIS
ON ANOTHER LEVEL?

19:41.349 --> 19:43.852
OKAY.

19:44.252 --> 19:46.421
[ SNIFFLES ]

19:46.421 --> 19:49.157
I CAN GO DOWN THERE WITH YOU.

20:00.134 --> 20:01.402
[ PILLS RATTLE ]

20:05.756 --> 20:07.864
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:07.864 --> 20:09.433
YOU LEFT YOUR PILLS OUT HERE,
AND I ‐‐

20:09.433 --> 20:11.335
GIVE ME THAT.

20:11.335 --> 20:13.537
I'M SORRY.
I WASN'T SNOOPING.

20:13.537 --> 20:14.605
GOOD.

20:14.605 --> 20:17.241
BECAUSE SNOOPING
WILL GET YOU FIRED.

20:27.551 --> 20:30.120
I KNOW
WHAT THOSE PILLS ARE.

20:30.120 --> 20:33.524
OH.
SO, YOU'RE A PHARMACIST NOW.

20:33.524 --> 20:36.026
I HAD BREAST CANCER, TOO.

20:36.026 --> 20:38.462
WHAT IS THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

20:40.464 --> 20:41.665
I USED TO WAKE UP

20:41.665 --> 20:44.134
WASHING THE BLOOD OUT OF
MY NIGHTGOWN JUST LIKE YOU.

20:44.134 --> 20:48.805
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

20:48.805 --> 20:52.142
OKAY.

20:52.142 --> 20:55.246
MAYBE I'M WRONG.

20:55.246 --> 20:59.015
IF I AM, IT'S A GOOD THING.

20:59.015 --> 21:01.652
I'M SORRY.

21:01.652 --> 21:05.222
I DIDN'T MEAN TO SEE
YOUR PILLS.

21:11.402 --> 21:13.169
HOW ARE YOU NOW?

21:16.273 --> 21:17.608
FINE.

21:17.608 --> 21:21.978
LOTS OF CHEMO
AND A MASTECTOMY.

21:21.978 --> 21:25.616
I THANK GOD
I'M CANCER‐FREE.

21:28.084 --> 21:30.186
WAS IT DIFFICULT?

21:30.186 --> 21:31.588
WHICH PART?

21:31.588 --> 21:33.724
THE SURGERY.

21:33.724 --> 21:36.493
IT'S THE MIND
THAT'S THE WEAPON.

21:36.493 --> 21:39.296
IT DOES MORE DAMAGE TO YOU
THAN THE CANCER.

21:52.008 --> 21:55.011
NO ONE KNOWS.

21:55.011 --> 21:57.614
NOT EVEN YOUR HUSBAND?

21:59.650 --> 22:01.151
NO.

22:05.322 --> 22:08.999
WELL, YOU'RE GONNA NEED
SOMEBODY TO BE THERE FOR YOU.

22:08.999 --> 22:11.935
I COULDN'T HAVE MADE IT
WITHOUT MY SON.

22:14.571 --> 22:16.973
I DON'T HAVE CHILDREN
THAT CARE ABOUT ME LIKE THAT.

22:18.675 --> 22:20.777
I'M SORRY.

22:20.777 --> 22:22.746
I KIND OF KNOW
WHAT YOU MEAN.

22:22.746 --> 22:26.750
IT'S SAD.

22:26.750 --> 22:28.184
I KNOW.

22:28.184 --> 22:32.323
WELL, EVERYBODY NEEDS
ONE GOOD PERSON IN THEIR LIFE.

22:32.323 --> 22:34.358
WHAT ABOUT MISS VERONICA?

22:34.358 --> 22:37.661
I'M MORE OF A FRIEND TO HER
THAN SHE IS TO ME.

22:37.661 --> 22:40.163
WELL, YOU CAN'T GET THROUGH THIS
ALONE.

22:40.163 --> 22:41.265
WHY NOT?

22:41.265 --> 22:44.435
IT'S HOW I GET THROUGH
EVERYTHING ELSE.

22:44.435 --> 22:47.471
WELL,
I'M HERE IF YOU NEED ME.

22:52.309 --> 22:54.878
THANK YOU.

22:54.878 --> 22:57.080
MM‐HMM.

22:57.080 --> 23:01.352
HANNA, MY FAMILY CANNOT
KNOW THIS ‐‐ NO ONE.

23:01.352 --> 23:05.289
MRS. CRYER...

23:05.289 --> 23:09.366
I TAKE MY EMPLOYER'S SECRETS
TO THE GRAVE.

23:09.366 --> 23:11.468
YES.

23:11.468 --> 23:13.169
I REMEMBER.

23:16.573 --> 23:18.074
HOW BAD IS IT?

23:18.074 --> 23:20.944
WE CAUGHT IT IN TIME.

23:20.944 --> 23:23.079
OH, GOOD.

23:23.079 --> 23:26.317
BUT MY HAIR'S
STARTING TO FALL OUT.

23:26.317 --> 23:27.918
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

23:27.918 --> 23:30.921
WE CAN GET YOU A NICE WIG.
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

23:30.921 --> 23:33.924
[ SNIFFLES ]
I HAVE A COUPLE.

23:33.924 --> 23:35.492
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:35.492 --> 23:39.330
HOW HAVE YOU BEEN GETTING
TO THE DOCTOR?

23:39.330 --> 23:40.797
I'VE BEEN DRIVING MYSELF.

23:40.797 --> 23:42.566
OH, NO.
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

23:42.566 --> 23:44.468
THE CHEMO MAKES YOU
TOO SICK.

23:44.468 --> 23:46.437
NOT ANYMORE, YOU'RE NOT.

23:49.340 --> 23:52.075
HOW DID YOU
KEEP YOUR SPIRITS UP?

23:52.075 --> 23:53.244
MM.

23:53.244 --> 23:54.511
PRAYER.

23:54.511 --> 23:56.780
SO, YOU'RE
A WOMAN OF FAITH.

23:56.780 --> 23:59.250
OH, YES, MA'AM, I AM.
I'M A CHRISTIAN.

23:59.250 --> 24:00.351
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:00.351 --> 24:02.052
THAT'S WONDERFUL.

24:08.732 --> 24:11.202
WOULD YOU PRAY FOR ME?

24:11.202 --> 24:13.036
Whew.

24:13.036 --> 24:15.772
OF COURSE.

24:15.772 --> 24:18.642
RIGHT NOW.

24:18.642 --> 24:21.144
OF COURSE.

24:27.418 --> 24:29.453
BOW YOUR HEAD.

24:32.489 --> 24:34.291
FATHER GOD, I COME BEFORE YOU
RIGHT NOW

24:34.291 --> 24:36.327
ON BEHALF OF
MY SISTER KATHERYN.

24:36.327 --> 24:39.129
LORD JESUS, WE ASK YOU TO
LOOK DOWN RIGHT NOW, LORD GOD,

24:39.129 --> 24:40.631
AND THROUGH YOUR BLOOD,

24:40.631 --> 24:44.000
WE ASK YOU TO TAKE THE POISON
THAT IS SUPPOSED TO BE HEALING

24:44.000 --> 24:45.536
AND GIVE IT THE POWER
THAT IS YOUR BLOOD,

24:45.536 --> 24:47.304
THAT IS THE TRUE HEALING.

24:47.304 --> 24:50.441
YOU SAID, "WHERE TWO OR THREE
ARE GATHERED IN YOUR NAME,

24:50.441 --> 24:51.708
THERE YOU ARE, ALSO."

24:51.708 --> 24:53.444
AND WE'RE NOT LOOKING FOR
REMISSION.

24:53.444 --> 24:55.312
LORD GOD, WE'RE LOOKING FOR
TRUE HEALING

24:55.312 --> 24:57.981
THAT ONLY YOU CAN PROVIDE.

24:57.981 --> 25:00.183
HEAL HER AS YOU HEALED ME,
LORD GOD.

25:00.183 --> 25:03.186
VICTORY AND HEALING
IS THE PRAYER.

25:03.186 --> 25:06.363
IN JESUS' NAME AND FOR HIS SAKE,
WE ARE PRAYING.

25:06.363 --> 25:07.364
AMEN.

25:27.551 --> 25:29.386
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:29.386 --> 25:31.021
WOW!

25:31.021 --> 25:34.024
LOOKS LIKE CHRISTMAS
HAS COME EARLY, HUH?

25:34.024 --> 25:36.760
YOU ASKED FOR IT.
I DID.

25:38.629 --> 25:41.698
THANK YOU, SIR.

25:41.698 --> 25:43.734
[ SIGHS ]

25:43.734 --> 25:46.370
SO, TELL ME
HOW THIS BABY WORKS.

25:51.875 --> 25:53.377
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

25:56.947 --> 25:59.816
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

26:10.901 --> 26:13.103
[ Telephone ringing ]

26:13.103 --> 26:14.871
IT'S DONE.

26:14.871 --> 26:17.208
MAKE IT HAPPEN.

26:17.208 --> 26:20.244
COUPLE DAYS IS FINE.

26:24.281 --> 26:26.683
OKAY.

26:26.683 --> 26:29.820
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

26:38.061 --> 26:40.464
[ DOG BARKING ]

26:46.002 --> 26:49.306
B., WHERE ARE YOU?

26:49.306 --> 26:51.842
BENNY BOY.

26:53.844 --> 26:55.712
WHY ARE YOU PACKING?

26:55.712 --> 26:57.548
DON'T.

26:57.548 --> 26:59.182
SO, YOU'RE MOVING?

26:59.182 --> 27:01.151
CANDACE, YOU KNOW
EXACTLY WHAT'S GOING ON. OKAY?

27:01.151 --> 27:03.119
DON'T TALK TO ME ABOUT
MOVING OUT OF THIS PLACE

27:03.119 --> 27:05.121
UNLESS YOU GOT THAT MONEY
YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT.

27:05.121 --> 27:07.798
IF YOU HAVEN'T NOTICED,
MAMA'S SICK.

27:07.798 --> 27:09.633
THIS IS SO SAD.

27:09.633 --> 27:13.069
YOU HAVEN'T SEEN SAD
TILL YOU'VE SEEN MAMA CRY.

27:13.069 --> 27:15.439
SHE WAS SO DISAPPOINTED IN ME,
CANDACE.

27:15.439 --> 27:18.375
WELL, NOW YOU KNOW HOW I FEEL.
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

27:18.375 --> 27:20.076
WHAT, ARE YOU ENJOYING THIS
OR SOMETHING?

27:20.076 --> 27:21.512
NO.

27:21.512 --> 27:23.514
MAYBE.

27:23.514 --> 27:24.581
JUST A LITTLE BIT.

27:24.581 --> 27:25.982
THAT IS
SO LOW‐DOWN OF YOU.

27:25.982 --> 27:27.251
YOU KNOW, I'M YOUR BROTHER.

27:27.251 --> 27:30.987
THAT'S YOUR MOTHER THAT
YOU'RE LAUGHING ABOUT RIGHT NOW.

27:30.987 --> 27:33.924
[ SCOFFS ]
I'M SO TIRED OF THIS.

27:33.924 --> 27:35.792
I'M TIRED OF YOU.

27:35.792 --> 27:37.928
ARE YOU DONE?
NO, I'M NOT.

27:37.928 --> 27:40.163
YOU KNOW WHAT?
MAYBE MAMA WAS RIGHT ABOUT YOU.

27:40.163 --> 27:41.732
YOU KNOW,
YOU HAVE NO RESPECT.

27:41.732 --> 27:43.800
YOU DON'T CARE ABOUT ANYBODY
BUT YOURSELF.

27:43.800 --> 27:46.837
SHE SAID THAT?

27:46.837 --> 27:48.104
YES, SHE SAID THAT.

27:48.104 --> 27:49.540
AND I'M STARTING
TO BELIEVE HER.

27:49.540 --> 27:51.608
YOU KNOW, I TOOK A MORTGAGE OUT
ON MAMA'S HOUSE ‐‐

27:51.608 --> 27:54.578
LOOK AT ME ‐‐
TO GET YOU OUT OF TROUBLE.

27:54.578 --> 27:56.613
AND YOU CAME IN HERE.

27:56.613 --> 27:58.048
YOU SWORE UP AND DOWN
THIS STREET,

27:58.048 --> 27:59.583
YOU WAS GONNA GET
THIS MORTGAGE PAID,

27:59.583 --> 28:01.285
AND NOW YOU GOT US
A COUPLE DAYS AWAY

28:01.285 --> 28:02.853
FROM BEING SENT OUT
ON THE STREET.

28:02.853 --> 28:04.821
HMM.

28:04.821 --> 28:06.423
SO, SHE REALLY THINKS

28:06.423 --> 28:09.666
THAT I DON'T CARE
ABOUT ANYBODY BUT MYSELF?

28:09.666 --> 28:11.568
YEAH.

28:15.772 --> 28:17.941
YOU BELIEVE THAT, TOO,
BENNY?

28:17.941 --> 28:21.445
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO THINK,
CANDACE?

28:21.445 --> 28:23.614
I MEAN, LOOK AT THE SITUATION
YOU GOT US IN.

28:23.614 --> 28:25.549
WE'VE BEEN IN THIS HOUSE
SINCE WE WERE KIDS.

28:25.549 --> 28:27.017
I HATED IT THEN.
I HATE IT NOW.

28:27.017 --> 28:28.252
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
MAMA LOVES IT, ALL RIGHT?

28:28.252 --> 28:29.453
THIS IS HER PRIDE AND JOY
RIGHT HERE.

28:29.453 --> 28:31.522
I DON'T CARE WHAT YOU LIKE.
IT'S A DUMP, BENNY.

28:31.522 --> 28:33.590
WHATEVER. IT'S HER DUMP.
SHE PAID FOR IT.

28:33.590 --> 28:36.293
LOOK, I DON'T WANT TO TALK ABOUT
THIS WITH YOU. YOU KNOW?

28:36.293 --> 28:37.794
I'M BEGINNING TO THINK

28:37.794 --> 28:39.563
YOU REALLY CAME DOWN HERE
TO ENJOY THIS MOMENT.

28:39.563 --> 28:40.831
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE SICK.

28:40.831 --> 28:43.700
BENNY, COME ON.
YOU KNOW ME.

28:43.700 --> 28:47.471
I THOUGHT
I KNEW YOU CANDACE.

28:47.471 --> 28:50.941
BUT THIS RIGHT HERE,

28:50.941 --> 28:54.911
IT SAYS A LOT ABOUT YOU,
LITTLE SISTER.

28:59.850 --> 29:04.755
BENNY, YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO BELIEVES IN ME,

29:04.755 --> 29:07.864
AND YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO LOVES ME.

29:09.833 --> 29:11.235
YOUR BABY LOVES YOU.

29:11.235 --> 29:12.736
I KNOW THAT.

29:12.736 --> 29:14.371
AND WHERE'S HE AT?
WHERE'S MY NEPHEW?

29:14.371 --> 29:17.341
HE'S WITH HIS FATHER.
I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT HIM.

29:17.341 --> 29:18.609
MAMA LOVES YOU.

29:18.609 --> 29:20.411
NO. MNH‐MNH.
SHE DOESN'T.

29:20.411 --> 29:21.678
SHE DOES, CANDACE.

29:21.678 --> 29:23.447
LOOK, I'M NOT GONNA DEBATE THAT
WITH YOU.

29:26.683 --> 29:28.719
LOOK, BENNY...

29:28.719 --> 29:33.056
BUT IF I DON'T HAVE YOU,
I DON'T HAVE ANYBODY.

29:42.132 --> 29:45.035
LOOK, CANDACE...

29:45.035 --> 29:46.303
I LOVE YOU.

29:46.303 --> 29:47.438
OKAY?
MM‐HMM.

29:47.438 --> 29:50.241
YOU'RE MY BABY SISTER.
YOU'RE MY ONLY SISTER.

29:50.241 --> 29:53.544
BUT WHAT YOU DID
AIN'T COOL.

29:53.544 --> 29:57.281
NOW, I'M SORRY,
BUT I'M PISSED OFF ABOUT THIS.

29:57.281 --> 29:58.915
ALL RIGHT?
MM‐HMM.

29:58.915 --> 30:00.817
YOU KNOW, YOU COME IN HERE,

30:00.817 --> 30:02.553
YOU TELL ME YOU GOT
SOME RICH MAN

30:02.553 --> 30:04.988
THAT'S IN LOVE WITH YOU,

30:04.988 --> 30:06.557
AND HE'S GONNA PAY
THIS MORTGAGE.

30:06.557 --> 30:08.499
YOU GET MY HOPES UP.
YOU KNOW, I TRUSTED YOU.

30:08.499 --> 30:10.234
THAT'S WHAT
I'M MOST PISSED OFF ABOUT.

30:10.234 --> 30:12.869
I TRUSTED YOU.

30:12.869 --> 30:15.306
AND THEN YOU WALK THROUGH
THE DOOR, YOU GET MY HOPES UP.

30:15.306 --> 30:16.673
NOTHING.

30:16.673 --> 30:19.943
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]
OKAY.

30:19.943 --> 30:22.346
THAT'S IT, CANDACE.

30:27.318 --> 30:30.354
YOU CALL THAT NOTHING?

30:30.354 --> 30:32.289
HMM?
WAIT, IS THIS ‐‐

30:32.289 --> 30:33.924
THIS IS ALL $50,000?
YEAH.

30:33.924 --> 30:36.026
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]
IT'S ALL OF IT.

30:36.026 --> 30:38.395
THANK YOU. THANK YOU.
THANK GOD.

30:38.395 --> 30:40.564
DON'T THANK GOD.
THANK ME, SWEETIE.

30:40.564 --> 30:42.032
SO, WAIT.
HE GAVE THIS TO YOU?

30:42.032 --> 30:43.033
WHO, GOD?

30:43.033 --> 30:44.601
NO, YOU'RE
RICH SUGAR‐DADDY FRIEND.

30:44.601 --> 30:46.870
YES.

30:46.870 --> 30:49.172
CANDACE, I'M NOT
GOING THROUGH THIS AGAIN.

30:49.172 --> 30:51.508
ARE YOU SURE THAT THIS SITUATION
IS LEGIT?

30:51.508 --> 30:52.576
YES.

30:52.576 --> 30:54.845
[ SNIFFS ]

30:54.845 --> 30:56.580
IS HE A DOPE BOY
OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

30:56.580 --> 30:57.714
IS THIS DOPE MONEY?
NO.

30:57.714 --> 31:00.050
HE'S IN THE LAW BUSINESS.
TRUST ME, B.

31:00.050 --> 31:01.985
IT'S REAL. IT'S LEGIT.

31:04.788 --> 31:06.397
JESUS.
WE GOT TO GET TO THE BANK.

31:06.397 --> 31:07.464
NO, NO, NO, NO.

31:07.464 --> 31:08.665
YOU GOT TO GET
SOME MONEY ORDERS.

31:08.665 --> 31:10.166
YOU CAN'T WALK IN A BANK
WITH ALL THIS CASH.

31:10.166 --> 31:11.235
THE IRS
WILL BE ALL OVER YOU.

31:11.235 --> 31:14.070
OKAY.

31:14.070 --> 31:17.241
[ SIGHS ]
CANDACE, THANK YOU.

31:17.241 --> 31:18.909
MAMA'S GONNA BE SO HAPPY.

31:18.909 --> 31:20.544
ALL RIGHT. COME ON.

31:20.544 --> 31:22.546
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE
BEFORE SHE COMES HOME.

31:22.546 --> 31:24.180
YOU KNOW
SHE DOESN'T WANT ME HERE.

31:24.180 --> 31:25.349
WILL YOU STOP IT?

31:25.349 --> 31:27.684
NO, YOU STOP LIVING IN
A FANTASY WORLD.

31:27.684 --> 31:29.286
SHE DOESN'T.

31:29.286 --> 31:31.087
COME ON.

31:31.087 --> 31:33.424
THANK YOU, BABY SISTER.

31:33.424 --> 31:34.858
YOU SAVED ME.

31:34.858 --> 31:37.060
THANK <i>YOU...</i>

31:37.928 --> 31:40.030
...FOR HELPING ME.

31:40.030 --> 31:42.433
I LOVE YOU.

31:42.433 --> 31:43.534
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]
LOVE YOU.

31:43.534 --> 31:45.135
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:45.135 --> 31:47.504
AH.

31:47.504 --> 31:49.873
WHAT ARE THOSE?
A KEY.

31:49.873 --> 31:51.275
TO WHAT?

31:51.275 --> 31:53.844
TO MY BRAND‐NEW CONVERTIBLE.

31:53.844 --> 31:55.145
HE GOT YOU THE CAR?

31:55.145 --> 31:56.480
[ Laughing ] YES.
I TOLD YOU.

31:56.480 --> 31:58.715
[ LAUGHS ] GIVE ME THESE.
I'M DRIVING.

31:58.715 --> 32:00.016
OH, B.!

32:00.016 --> 32:02.052
AS IF YOU WERE GOING TO.

32:02.052 --> 32:04.655
[ LAUGHS ]

32:08.732 --> 32:10.901
COME ON IN AND LIE DOWN.
[ SIGHS ]

32:10.901 --> 32:13.169
I DON'T FEEL LIKE LYING DOWN,
HANNA.

32:16.307 --> 32:18.842
THE DOCTOR SAID
TAKE THESE FOR NAUSEA.

32:18.842 --> 32:20.744
THEY DON'T WORK.

32:20.744 --> 32:23.013
WELL, MAYBE YOU SHOULD UP
THE DOSAGE.

32:23.013 --> 32:24.848
HANNA, DON'T MAKE A FUSS.

32:24.848 --> 32:26.650
I JUST WANT YOU TO BE
COMFORTABLE.

32:26.650 --> 32:29.386
WHY?
WHY WHAT?

32:29.386 --> 32:31.888
WHY DO YOU WANT ME
TO BE COMFORTABLE?

32:31.888 --> 32:33.724
BECAUSE YOU'RE ONE
OF GOD'S CHILDREN.

32:33.724 --> 32:35.392
AM I?

32:35.392 --> 32:37.093
YES.

32:37.093 --> 32:39.696
WELL, GOD MUST NOT BE
VERY PLEASED WITH ME,

32:39.696 --> 32:41.665
OR HE WOULDN'T HAVE GIVEN ME
CANCER.

32:41.665 --> 32:43.400
GOD DIDN'T GIVE YOU
CANCER.

32:43.400 --> 32:45.101
THEN WHERE DID IT
COME FROM?

32:45.101 --> 32:46.437
I DON'T KNOW.

32:48.672 --> 32:51.174
I DO BELIEVE
THAT HOLDING ON TO BAD THINGS,

32:51.174 --> 32:52.809
LIKE UNFORGIVENESS AND ANGER,

32:52.809 --> 32:54.278
HOLDING ALL THAT
IS BAD IN YOUR HEART

32:54.278 --> 32:56.179
AND CAN LEAD TO SICKNESS
IN THE BODY.

32:56.179 --> 32:59.683
WELL, IF THAT WERE THE CASE,
I'D BE DEAD.

32:59.683 --> 33:01.785
[ LAUGHS ]

33:01.785 --> 33:04.255
HMM.

33:04.255 --> 33:06.257
WHAT?
LOOK AT YOU.

33:06.257 --> 33:07.531
[ Chuckling ] WHAT?

33:07.531 --> 33:10.234
I BELIEVE THAT'S THE FIRST TIME
I'VE SEEN YOU LAUGH.

33:10.234 --> 33:14.104
YOU DON'T LAUGH MUCH, HANNA.
HMM.

33:14.104 --> 33:15.372
ARE YOU HAPPY?

33:15.372 --> 33:19.810
I TRY TO KEEP JOY
IN MY HEART.

33:19.810 --> 33:21.745
BUT IT'S BEEN HARD LATELY.

33:21.745 --> 33:24.147
WHY?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

33:24.147 --> 33:29.185
OH, I AM NOT ABOUT TO TELL YOU
MY PROBLEMS.

33:29.185 --> 33:30.454
WHY NOT?

33:30.454 --> 33:33.557
'CAUSE USUALLY WHEN PEOPLE ASK
WHAT'S GOING ON,

33:33.557 --> 33:35.759
THEY DON'T REALLY WANT
TO KNOW.

33:35.759 --> 33:37.928
I DO.

33:37.928 --> 33:42.966
WELL, USUALLY...THEY START OUT
WANTING TO KNOW,

33:42.966 --> 33:44.868
BUT PRETTY SOON,
THEY HATE TO SEE YOU COMING,

33:44.868 --> 33:47.271
ESPECIALLY IF YOU'VE GOT
A LOT OF DRAMA.

33:47.271 --> 33:50.541
YOU HAVE A LOT OF DRAMA?

33:53.277 --> 33:55.779
NOT AS MUCH AS YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:55.779 --> 33:57.948
WELL,
MY FAMILY IS SOMETHING.

33:57.948 --> 33:59.516
YES, THEY ARE.

33:59.516 --> 34:02.553
THANK YOU.
DON'T MENTION IT.

34:06.122 --> 34:07.898
HANNA, I REALLY DO
APPRECIATE THIS.

34:09.366 --> 34:10.601
I NEED YOU
TO UNDERSTAND ‐‐

34:10.601 --> 34:14.538
MRS. CRYER, YOU DON'T HAVE TO
SAY ANYTHING.

34:14.538 --> 34:16.873
I WORK FOR YOU.

34:16.873 --> 34:18.975
I'M NOT YOUR FRIEND.

34:18.975 --> 34:20.176
I GET IT.

34:20.176 --> 34:23.880
THAT'S NOT
WHAT I WAS GONNA SAY.

34:23.880 --> 34:25.816
THEN WHAT WAS IT?

34:27.684 --> 34:30.120
COME HERE.

34:40.030 --> 34:44.635
I WAS GOING TO SAY THAT YOU
HAVE BEEN KINDER TO ME...

34:44.635 --> 34:46.603
TODAY...

34:46.603 --> 34:50.941
THAN MY WHOLE FAMILY
OR ANY OF MY FRIENDS HAVE BEEN.

34:55.512 --> 34:58.249
WELL, YOU CAN'T PICK
YOUR FAMILY,

34:58.249 --> 35:00.651
BUT YOU DO NEED
SOME NEW FRIENDS.

35:00.651 --> 35:02.686
[ CHUCKLES ]
WELL.

35:02.686 --> 35:04.688
COME ON,
PUT YOUR FEET UP.

35:04.688 --> 35:07.298
NO.

35:07.298 --> 35:09.433
YOU KNOW THIS IS BEYOND
YOUR JOB DESCRIPTION.

35:09.433 --> 35:10.901
SO, I CAN'T BE NICE TO YOU

35:10.901 --> 35:13.169
BECAUSE IT'S NOT
IN MY JOB DESCRIPTION?

35:13.169 --> 35:14.605
OF COURSE YOU CAN.

35:14.605 --> 35:17.274
I'M JUST SAYING,
THIS IS BEYOND THE CALL OF DUTY.

35:17.274 --> 35:18.775
YOU DO KNOW I KNOW THAT,
DON'T YOU?

35:18.775 --> 35:20.277
YES, BUT I WAS ‐‐

35:20.277 --> 35:22.746
OH, PLEASE DON'T SAY WHY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:22.746 --> 35:24.215
YOU MUST BE AROUND

35:24.215 --> 35:27.551
A LOT OF PEOPLE WHO DO THINGS
FOR A REASON.

35:27.551 --> 35:30.687
SOMETIMES PEOPLE ARE JUST KIND,
MRS. CRYER.

35:30.687 --> 35:34.291
WELL, YOU ARE VERY KIND.

35:34.291 --> 35:35.892
HMM.

35:35.892 --> 35:39.263
YOU ARE A GENTLE SOUL.

35:39.263 --> 35:41.265
Whew.

35:41.265 --> 35:42.799
COME REST.

35:42.799 --> 35:44.568
I'LL MAKE YOU SOME TEA.

35:46.503 --> 35:47.938
BRANDY.

35:47.938 --> 35:49.640
TEA.

35:49.640 --> 35:51.342
SCOTCH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:51.342 --> 35:55.045
TEA.
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:55.045 --> 35:56.247
OH, FINE.

35:56.247 --> 35:59.182
YOU CAN'T MIX THAT
WITH THIS MEDICATION.

36:02.819 --> 36:05.289
[ DOOR OPENS ]

36:05.289 --> 36:08.565
TEA.

36:08.565 --> 36:11.402
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

36:21.945 --> 36:24.748
LORD, LORD, LORD.

36:24.748 --> 36:26.683
YOU SAY SOMETHING?

36:26.683 --> 36:29.253
I WAS TALKING TO
THE LORD.

36:29.253 --> 36:30.521
OH.

36:30.521 --> 36:32.055
WELL, WHAT DID HE SAY?

36:33.890 --> 36:35.892
YOU THINK THIS IS FUNNY,
BENNY?

36:35.892 --> 36:38.495
NO, MA'AM.
NOT AT ALL.

36:42.233 --> 36:44.134
YOU HAVEN'T
FINISHED PACKING YET.

36:44.134 --> 36:46.069
NOPE.

36:46.069 --> 36:48.539
GUESS
I HAVE TO DO THAT, TOO.

36:50.874 --> 36:52.876
WAIT.

36:52.876 --> 36:55.212
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND.

36:55.212 --> 36:57.448
OHH.
BENNY, I AM NOT IN THE MOOD.

37:00.251 --> 37:02.786
I JUST WANTED TO SAY
I'M SORRY

37:02.786 --> 37:04.888
AND ASK YOU TO FORGIVE ME.

37:07.331 --> 37:09.199
WOULD YOU DO THAT?

37:14.638 --> 37:18.875
BOY, I ALREADY FORGAVE YOU
BEFORE YOU DID IT.

37:18.875 --> 37:22.212
THAT'S WHAT
UNCONDITIONAL LOVE IS.

37:22.212 --> 37:25.416
I LOVE YOU, SON.

37:25.416 --> 37:28.419
I REALLY DO.

37:28.419 --> 37:31.087
BUT THIS IS ONE OF
THE LOWEST THINGS

37:31.087 --> 37:33.023
ANYBODY HAS EVER DONE TO ME.

37:33.023 --> 37:37.294
I'M ALMOST 50 YEARS OLD,
AND I'M ABOUT TO BE HOMELESS.

37:37.294 --> 37:38.762
[ SCOFFS ]

37:38.762 --> 37:43.667
I CAN'T EVEN BEGIN
TO THINK ABOUT STARTING OVER.

37:43.667 --> 37:48.472
I INTENDED TO DIE
IN THIS HOUSE.

37:50.741 --> 37:52.276
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

37:52.276 --> 37:54.811
WELL, I WAS HOPING YOU'D GET TO
LIVE IN IT FOR AT LEAST ANOTHER,

37:54.811 --> 37:58.749
I DON'T KNOW,
50, 60, MAYBE EVEN 70 YEARS.

37:58.749 --> 37:59.916
WHO KNOWS?

37:59.916 --> 38:02.286
WELL,
I WISH TO HEAVEN I COULD.

38:06.430 --> 38:09.633
HOW'D YOU DO THIS?

38:15.239 --> 38:17.408
YOUR TRUCK IS STILL OUTSIDE.
YOU DIDN'T SELL IT.

38:17.408 --> 38:18.875
HOW'D YOU DO THIS?

38:18.875 --> 38:21.011
CANDACE GAVE ME THE MONEY.

38:21.011 --> 38:22.779
HOW'D SHE GET $50,000?

38:22.779 --> 38:25.048
MAMA, DON'T.

38:25.048 --> 38:27.518
I DON'T WANT THAT GIRL GETTING
KILLED TRYING TO SAVE MY HOUSE.

38:27.518 --> 38:28.519
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:28.519 --> 38:30.554
I'M SO GLAD
YOU SAID THAT.

38:30.554 --> 38:32.923
THAT MEANS YOU WOULD HAVE
MORTGAGED THIS HOUSE

38:32.923 --> 38:33.990
TO HELP CANDACE OUT.

38:33.990 --> 38:36.660
OH, HUSH.
YOU DON'T KNOW NOTHING.

38:36.660 --> 38:38.194
WHERE'D SHE GET
THIS MONEY FROM?

38:38.194 --> 38:39.263
I DON'T KNOW.

38:39.263 --> 38:41.965
SHE SAID SHE HAS
SOME, UH, RICH MAN.

38:41.965 --> 38:43.234
HE GAVE IT TO HER.
A DRUG DEALER?

38:43.234 --> 38:44.701
NO, SHE SAID
HE WAS IN THE LAW BUSINESS.

38:44.701 --> 38:45.769
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

38:45.769 --> 38:47.804
I DON'T KNOW, MAMA,
BUT SHE GOT IT.

38:47.804 --> 38:49.139
OH, BENNY,
YOU KNOW I DON'T ‐‐

38:49.139 --> 38:51.442
DON'T YOU DARE SAY
THAT YOU DON'T WANT IT, MAMA.

38:51.442 --> 38:54.211
IT'S NOT DIRTY MONEY.
I TALKED TO HER, OKAY?

38:54.211 --> 38:56.413
IT'S THE MONEY
THAT SHE OWED YOU.

38:56.413 --> 38:58.382
NOW YOUR HOUSE IS PAID.

38:58.382 --> 39:01.285
IT'S PAID?

39:01.285 --> 39:06.330
YOUR DEED, YOUR NAME,

39:06.330 --> 39:07.864
WITHOUT MY NAME,

39:07.864 --> 39:11.134
SO YOU DON'T EVER HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT ME MORTGAGING IT AGAIN.

39:11.134 --> 39:13.670
IT'S PAID OFF.

39:13.670 --> 39:16.907
I GET TO KEEP MY HOUSE?

39:16.907 --> 39:19.543
YOU GET TO KEEP YOUR HOUSE,
MOMMY.

39:19.543 --> 39:21.312
[ SOBS ]
TOLD YOU I GOT YOU.

39:21.312 --> 39:23.580
YEAH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:23.580 --> 39:27.083
THANK YOU, JESUS.
HALLELUJAH! OH!

39:27.083 --> 39:28.852
PRAISE GOD.

39:28.852 --> 39:30.921
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

39:30.921 --> 39:33.357
MWAH!
OH!

39:33.357 --> 39:35.392
NOW CAN WE UNPACK, PLEASE?

39:35.392 --> 39:37.027
YES, WE CAN, ABSOLUTELY.

39:37.027 --> 39:38.995
YOU'RE GONNA SEND ME
INTO A HEART ATTACK OVER HERE.

39:38.995 --> 39:40.664
COME ON.

39:40.664 --> 39:43.967
OH!
[ LAUGHS ]

39:43.967 --> 39:46.303
I AIN'T NEVER LIKED
THESE PLACE MATS.

39:46.303 --> 39:48.372
AND THAT BIG CHICKEN.
[ LAUGHS ]

39:51.808 --> 39:53.877
Veronica:
KNOCK, KNOCK.

39:53.877 --> 39:56.213
YES?

39:56.213 --> 40:00.384
WHY ARE YOU IN THIS BED
EVERY TIME I COME OVER HERE?

40:00.384 --> 40:03.320
UGH.
I'VE BEEN UP LATE NIGHTS.

40:03.320 --> 40:05.222
WELL, HONEY, GET UP.

40:05.222 --> 40:06.830
I HAVE A CRISIS.

40:06.830 --> 40:08.799
WHAT IS IT NOW?

40:08.799 --> 40:11.568
DON'T SAY IT LIKE THAT.

40:11.568 --> 40:13.136
THIS IS SERIOUS.

40:13.136 --> 40:15.206
I'M SORRY.

40:15.206 --> 40:17.408
WHAT IS IT?

40:17.408 --> 40:20.777
I WAS FEELING UNEASY
ABOUT DAVID.

40:20.777 --> 40:23.980
I KNOW.
YOU TOLD ME THAT.

40:23.980 --> 40:26.583
I THOUGHT
HE WAS HAVING AN AFFAIR.

40:26.583 --> 40:29.185
YOU ALSO TOLD ME THAT.

40:29.185 --> 40:33.023
WELL, A GIRL
HAS GOT TO FOLLOW HER GUT.

40:33.023 --> 40:35.592
WELL, WHAT DID THE GIRL DO?

40:35.592 --> 40:39.963
I CALLED MARTY,

40:39.963 --> 40:42.433
A PRIVATE EYE
THAT WE USE FROM TIME TO TIME

40:42.433 --> 40:44.768
TO HELP WITH SOME OF
OUR REHAB PATIENTS.

40:44.768 --> 40:46.737
OKAY.

40:54.311 --> 40:56.347
IS THIS CANDACE?

40:56.347 --> 40:58.682
YES.

40:58.682 --> 41:01.718
I KNEW THERE WAS SOMETHING UP
WITH THAT GIRL.

41:01.718 --> 41:03.287
WHEN DID DAVID MEET HER?

41:03.287 --> 41:05.522
I DON'T KNOW.

41:05.522 --> 41:08.499
HE PRETENDED TO MEET HER
FOR THE FIRST TIME

41:08.499 --> 41:11.167
HERE AT YOUR HOUSE.

41:11.167 --> 41:13.570
I AM SO PISSED.

41:13.570 --> 41:16.039
THIS IS VERY ODD
FOR DAVID.

41:16.039 --> 41:18.575
THIS CAN'T BE SERIOUS.

41:18.575 --> 41:21.845
[ SCOFFS ]
HE BOUGHT HER A CAR.

41:21.845 --> 41:22.913
WHAT?

41:22.913 --> 41:26.082
IT'S RIGHT THERE
IN THE PICTURES.

41:28.752 --> 41:30.921
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO?

41:30.921 --> 41:36.227
I'M GOING TO PAY
THE LITTLE BITCH A VISIT.

41:40.664 --> 41:42.433
<i>NEXT, ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS."</i>

41:42.433 --> 41:43.534
I'M BENNY.

41:43.534 --> 41:45.436
DARCI.
DARCI FROM THE CHURCH?

41:45.436 --> 41:47.371
IS THAT WHAT I THINK IT IS?

41:47.371 --> 41:49.506
I SMELLED MARIJUANA.
NO, YOU DIDN'T.

41:49.506 --> 41:52.743
YOU NEE‐‐
YOU NEED TO ZIP THIS BACK UP.

41:52.743 --> 41:54.077
WELL, SHE IS VERY,
VERY GOOD AT SEX.

41:54.077 --> 41:55.912
WHAT IS SHE DOING HERE?

41:55.912 --> 41:57.180
I KNOW ABOUT THE CAR.

41:57.180 --> 41:58.249
WHAT CAR?

41:58.249 --> 41:59.583
THE ONE YOU BOUGHT FOR HER.

41:59.583 --> 42:01.718
YOU THINK I'M SLEEPING
WITH YOUR HUSBAND,

42:01.718 --> 42:03.720
AND YOU THINK YOUR SON
IS STRAIGHT.

42:03.720 --> 42:05.622
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU MAKE
A PERSONAL VISIT

42:05.622 --> 42:07.631
UNLESS THERE WAS SOMETHING WRONG
WITH ONE OF THE PATIENTS.

42:07.631 --> 42:10.501
NO, SON,
THIS VISIT IS ABOUT <i>YOU.</i>
